        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Show LiteLLM budget spend details",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Show LiteLLM personal and team spend/budget amounts directly on the budget rows while preserving reset time text.\n- Hide the duplicate budgeted LiteLLM extra usage section, while keeping spend-only API spend visible.\n- Redact visible metric text when Hide Personal Info is enabled, so LiteLLM team aliases cannot leak through budget detail rows.\n- Add regression coverage for LiteLLM budget row details, duplicate cost suppression, and personal-info redaction.\n\n## After-fix proof\n- RED: `swift test --filter LiteLLMMenuCardModelTests` failed before the redaction fix because the LiteLLM team detail still showed an email-shaped team alias.\n- GREEN: `swift test --filter LiteLLMMenuCardModelTests` passed 3 tests after the fix, with the redacted team detail rendered as `Team Hidden: $70.00 / $1,000.00`.\n- Broader model proof: `swift test --filter MenuCardModelTests` passed 48 tests across 13 suites after the fix.\n\n## Test Plan\n- [x] `swift test --filter LiteLLMMenuCardModelTests`\n- [x] `swift test --filter MenuCardModelTests`\n- [x] `swift test --filter MenuCardKiloPassTests`\n- [x] `swift test --filter MenuDescriptorKiloTests`\n- [x] `.build/lint-tools/bin/swiftformat Sources Tests --lint`\n- [x] `.build/lint-tools/bin/swiftlint --strict`\n- [x] `git diff --check`\n\n## Notes\n- `./Scripts/lint.sh lint` currently fails locally on `docs/site.js` because `node --check` treats it as CommonJS while the file uses an ESM `import`. This failure is outside the files changed here.\n",
